1
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:14,920
What do you need me to help you with?

2
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:16,960
I went through all the Marquis Manor's accounts

3
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,760
and found a suspicious sum of silver flowing into the Manor.

4
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,690
How much silver?

5
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,240
A full 500,000 taels.

6
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,480
That much?

7
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,930
500,000 taels covers the army's pay for over half a year.

8
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,160
I remember the Imperial Court

9
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:32,020
allocated 500,000 taels to the Song Army back then.

10
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:33,560
That's right.

11
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,720
But even when the Song Army ran out of supplies

12
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,759
and was wiped out,

13
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,450
that money was never found.

14
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,650
Father, please let me go to the border with you

15
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,960
to live and die alongside the Song Army.

16
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,080
The Emperor has decreed

17
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,080
that you must remain in the capital.

18
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:53,800
The Emperor is keeping me as a hostage.

19
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,080
Punishment or reward,

20
00:01:56,479 --> 00:01:58,140
it is all His Majesty's grace.

21
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,140
I accept the order.

22
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,720
Miss.

23
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,480
Miss.

24
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:22,160
The Song Army's provisions have been intercepted by the enemy.

25
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,600
They've been without food for three days.

26
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,360
The soldiers are exhausted.

27
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,079
They tried to break out last night,

28
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,160
but were ambushed.

29
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,520
As a result,

30
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,520
the General and the Young General are trapped.

31
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,840
Their fate is unknown.

32
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,560
If there are no reinforcements,

33
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,760
the Song Army won't last.

34
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:45,840
Miss! Miss!

35
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,480
Miss!

36
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,480
I'm going to the border.

37
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:58,079
Miss, have you forgotten?

38
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,840
The Emperor issued a decree.

39
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,840
You cannot leave.

40
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,600
By the Emperor's decree.

41
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,240
In the great battle at the border,

42
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:22,280
General Song and Young General Song led 30,000 soldiers

43
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,800
in a bloody battle.

44
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:29,600
Though they have fallen, their loyalty shall be immortalized in history.

45
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,360
After the battle,

46
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,000
the Kingdom of Yueshi seeks peace.

47
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:36,720
This is a blessing for the world.

48
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,560
His Majesty is benevolent

49
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,920
and wishes to seize this opportunity

50
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:43,280
to bring peace and prosperity to the nation.

51
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,040
Respect this.

52
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,600
So His Majesty means,

53
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:53,200
the lives of over 30,000 Song Army soldiers

54
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,920
are to be written off just like that?

55
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:57,440
Prime Minister Shen had an audience with His Majesty.

56
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,360
He also wants to prioritize peace.

57
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:02,280
Besides, Marquis Bai, without permission,

58
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,880
took troops to the border of his own accord.

59
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,880
He has already angered His Majesty.

60
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,760
At this time, you must remember His Majesty's grace.

61
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:13,520
Do not cause any more trouble.

62
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,840
The origin of this silver is vague.

63
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,920
The ledger lists it as a special subsidy,

64
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,640
but no official document for the allocation can be found.

65
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:58,170
I remember back then, only the Song Army and Bai Army needed pay.

66
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:01,340
I didn't suspect the Zhongyi Marquis Manor.

67
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,880
Father, where are you going?

68
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:07,920
I'm going to bring Brother Song and the Song Army home.

69
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,780
But the Emperor didn't order you to go to the border.

70
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,920
Even so,

71
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,720
I must go.

72
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:16,840
Our Bai Army's banner cannot be stained by any blemish.

73
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:22,040
I know the Marquis Manor's accounts fairly well.

74
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,960
If a large sum suddenly appeared in the Manor,

75
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,360
I would definitely know.

76
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,840
But the strange thing is,

77
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,040
I've never seen this silver.

78
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,720
You mean,

79
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,640
although it's recorded in the Manor's books,

80
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:33,920
it never actually entered the treasury?

81
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,680
This silver might just be a bookkeeping entry, a phantom transfer,

82
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,560
without actual deposit.

83
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,680
In other words,

84
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:42,120
the Marquis Manor became a shell to hide the missing silver.

85
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,920
Then where did the real silver go?

86
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,840
It might have been hijacked during transit,

87
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:49,080
or someone forged the accounts to make it look like

88
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:49,920
it entered the Manor,

89
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,980
but actually diverted it elsewhere.

90
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:53,440
Regardless of the theory,

91
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,960
only insiders could pull this off.

92
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:59,540
Only the Manor's accountant and the military dispatcher.

93
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,280
That is to say,

94
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,960
the Song Army pay embezzlement case

95
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:08,080
was a premeditated conspiracy from the start,

96
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,480
using the Marquis Manor to launder the accounts.

97
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,740
I can't tolerate that.

98
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:15,760
Bai Manchuan, are you sure you want to investigate with me?

99
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,440
I'm sure.

100
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,920
And certain.

101
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,480
Your Highness has come from afar.

102
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,040
I welcome you with a song

103
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,220
to show my respect.

104
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:33,920
You women of Dasheng always love to speak useless words.

105
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:37,640
Do you think plucking a few strings will please me?

106
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,640
If Your Highness is displeased,

107
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,760
I can also dance to please you.

108
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:54,520
Since you are the top courtesan of Baihua Tower,

109
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,600
you should know what men want.

110
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,000
Your Highness, no. Don't.

111
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,840
You're just a lowly thing.

112
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,170
How dare you negotiate with me?

113
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:14,640
Aren't you here just to please me?

114
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,320
Either serve me well,

115
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,680
or die.

116
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,480
I will obey Your Highness.

117
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,600
Brother.

118
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,040
Now that you're here,

119
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,800
my mood is ruined.

120
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,480
Get out.

121
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,360
Have you forgotten your place?

122
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:45,480
I dare not forget.

123
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,880
You are just a helper Mother sent to me.

124
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,640
Know your place.

125
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,730
Don't dream of escaping your fate.

126
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:56,000
Your every move must serve me.

127
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:01,520
Then what do you need me to do?

128
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,160
I will tell you when it's time to act.

129
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,600
Don't take matters into your own hands.

130
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,040
As you wish.

131
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,220
Spirits of the Grassland,

132
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,920
if you can hear me,

133
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,080
please guide me.

134
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,700
Tell me the location of the Grassland Queen.

135
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:26,570
You will find her at the Dasheng Literary Gathering.

136
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,120
Is this the way?

137
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,480
It should be.

138
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:38,610
Why haven't Brother and Sister-in-law arrived yet?

139
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:39,919
Sister,

140
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:42,600
I want to go back to the Marquis Manor.

141
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,159
I want to go back too.

142
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,640
Don't be afraid. I'm here.

143
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,520
Why haven't Brother and Sister-in-law arrived yet?

144
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,160
Are they taking this road?

145
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,720
Isn't this Bai Chaohua?

146
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:55,800
Why are you here too?

147
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,440
Isn't this Shen Qiangwei?

148
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,570
Why are you here too?

149
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:01,120
A mere daughter of a military man,

150
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:04,420
I bet you can't even read all the words at the gathering.

151
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,320
It's better than reeking of powder.

152
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,600
You smell like a common spice seller.

153
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,600
Don't be so arrogant, Bai Chaohua.

154
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,680
I'll be as arrogant as I please.

155
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,480
What are you going to do about it?

156
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,480
I know you're here for the Third Prince.

157
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:20,000
But anyone could figure it out.

158
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:23,410
Why would the Third Prince like someone as vulgar as you?

159
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:27,160
A sparrow like you wants to become a phoenix?

160
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,720
I should be the one saying that.

161
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,200
Why would the Third Prince like

162
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,640
an empty-headed idiot like you?

163
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,360
Sister,

164
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,640
Let's ignore her.

165
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,920
Let's go home.

166
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:35,760
No.

167
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:38,640
I'm going to beat this idiot to the ground today.

168
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,880
Who are you calling an idiot?

169
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,080
I mean you.

170
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,040
You flatter me.

171
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,440
You dare hit me?

172
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,640
You shrew!

173
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,360
Hmph. That's right.

174
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,160
I'll show you what a real shrew looks like.

175
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:49,720
Stop fighting!

176
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,480
What a real shrew is!

177
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,400
Stay here and watch Sister Chaohua.

178
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,960
I'll go get Brother and Sister-in-law.

179
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,820
Stop fighting!

180
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,040
Stop fighting!

181
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,640
Sister, stop fighting!

182
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,600
Let go!

183
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,240
Sister!

184
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,520
I'm going to beat her down today!

185
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,000
Stop it, Miss.

186
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:04,520
Let go!
